column4: I found myself getting upset by quite trivial things because I have been feeling overwhelmed with work and personal issues, making minor inconveniences feel more significant than they are.
I was aware of dryness of my mouth occasionally, likely due to stress and not staying properly hydrated throughout the day.
I couldn't seem to experience any positive feeling at all as the constant pressure and strained relationships have left me feeling emotionally drained and unable to find joy in daily activities.
I did not experience breathing difficulty except during certain moments of heightened stress when I felt my chest tightening.
I just couldn't seem to get going because the lack of motivation and feeling of being unappreciated has left me feeling stuck and uninspired.
I tended to over-react to situations as my tolerance for stress has decreased significantly and small issues now feel like major setbacks.
I had a feeling of shakiness briefly during particularly stressful encounters, but it did not persist throughout the week.
I found it difficult to relax as the constant pressure and feeling of being undervalued have kept my mind racing even in moments of supposed rest.
I found myself in situations that made me so anxious I was most relieved when they ended, highlighting the high levels of anxiety and discomfort I have been experiencing in various interactions.
I felt that I had nothing to look forward to because the strained relationships and lack of recognition have left me feeling disheartened about the future.
I found myself getting upset rather easily as the ongoing stressors have lowered my threshold for frustration and disappointment.
I felt that I was using a lot of nervous energy, especially during high-pressure moments, but it was not a constant feeling throughout the week.
I felt sad and depressed due to the continuous strain in relationships and the sense of not being valued for my work and efforts.
I found myself getting impatient when I was delayed in any way, reflecting a growing sense of irritability and impatience with minor inconveniences.
I had a feeling of faintness briefly during moments of intense stress, likely due to shallow breathing and lack of proper relaxation.
I felt that I had lost interest in just about everything because the constant tension and feeling of being undervalued have drained my enthusiasm for my work and daily activities.
I felt I wasn't worth much as a person mainly due to the lack of respect and recognition I have been receiving from students and colleagues, leading to a sense of diminished self-worth.
I felt that I was rather touchy due to the ongoing stress and strain in relationships, making me more sensitive to comments and behaviors from others.
I perspired noticeably in the absence of high temperatures during moments of intense anxiety and stress, causing physical symptoms of discomfort.
I felt scared without any good reason at times, likely due to the overall sense of unease and tension in my interactions with others.
I felt that life wasn't worthwhile because of the persistent feeling of being undervalued and unappreciated, leading to a lack of purpose and fulfillment.
I found it hard to wind down as the constant thoughts about work, strained relationships, and lack of recognition have kept my mind racing even during moments of rest.
I had difficulty in swallowing briefly during moments of heightened stress, likely due to tension and anxiety.
I couldn't seem to get any enjoyment out of the things I did because the ongoing strain in relationships and lack of recognition have overshadowed any sense of pleasure or satisfaction.
I was aware of the action of my heart in the absence of physical exertion during stressful situations, leading to a heightened awareness of my physical responses to stress.
I felt down-hearted and blue due to the cumulative effect of feeling undervalued, unappreciated, and emotionally drained from strained relationships.
I found that I was very irritable, especially in situations where I felt disrespected or unacknowledged, leading to outbursts of frustration and impatience.
I felt I was close to panic during certain high-pressure moments, but I was able to manage this feeling without it escalating further.
I found it hard to calm down after something upset me because the ongoing stressors and feeling of being unappreciated have kept my mind in a state of unease and tension.
